+3. Pin the standard React Testing Library packages, replace the source/static child proxy with tests mounting the default `AppraisalWorkbench`, and remove the React status/provenance workflow matrix so backend `enabled` is authoritative with `/auth/me` permission/role intersection only as a usability guard.
+4. Run focused green tests, dependency scan, then all configured frontend and backend gates with the mandated Python interpreter. Save self-contained logs and exact HTTP examples.
+5. Review the diff for protected paths and scope, produce changed-files/risk/review/final artifacts, update slice/state/progress/handoff, and sharpen the next one or two eligible Not Started slices using only already-opened source extracts.
+
